    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This museum-grade 2001 BMW M3 (E46) represents a pinnacle of analog performance. Under the hood lies the S54B32 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure dual-VANOS system to deliver linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and sent to the rear wheels through a factory M-Variable Differential Lock. The chassis is structurally immaculate, featuring professional subframe reinforcement and pristine bushings. Every mechanical component, from the MacPherson strut front architecture to the multi-link rear setup, remains in factory-spec alignment. This is a rare, turn-key example for the purist who demands mechanical perfection.",
